<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>FEI TeamArt · Foundation of Sketch A · Lesson 2: Sphere in the Real World</title>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Montserrat:wght@400;500;700;800;900&family=Open+Sans:wght@400;500;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">

<style>
  /* ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
     FEI TeamArt · Lesson 2 Placeholder
     ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
     This is a temporary placeholder for Lesson 2: Sphere in the Real World.
     The pedagogy: after learning the abstract sphere in Lesson 1,
     students will pick a real-world spherical object (apple vs. orange)
     and apply form/light principles to it.
     
     For now, this page shows "Coming Soon" with the FEI design language
     and lets students return to Lesson 1 or navigate forward.
     ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */
  
  :root {
    --ink: #1a1d2b;
    --ink-soft: rgba(26, 29, 43, 0.65);
    --ink-faint: rgba(26, 29, 43, 0.45);
    --paper: #fafaf8;
    --gold: #c8a96e;
    --purple: #a78bfa;
    --green: #1d9e75;
    --gradient-bg: linear-gradient(135deg, #e9d8fd 0%, #d4e6ff 50%, #cffafe 100%);
  }
  
  * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
  
  body {
    font-family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif;
    background: var(--gradient-bg);
    color: var(--ink);
    min-height: 100vh;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    padding: 40px 20px;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  
  .container {
    max-width: 640px;
    width: 100%;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
    backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
    border-radius: 24px;
    padding: 48px 40px;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 30px rgba(26, 29, 43, 0.08);
    text-align: center;
  }
  
  .kicker {
    font-family: 'Montserrat', sans-serif;
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 3px;
    color: var(--purple);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  
  .lesson-number {
    font-family: 'Montserrat', sans-serif;
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    letter-spacing: 1.5px;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  
  h1 {
    font-family: 'Montserrat', sans-serif;
    font-size: 36px;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--ink);
    letter-spacing: -0.5px;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }
  
  .visual {
    margin: 32px auto;
    max-width: 200px;
  }
  
  .visual svg {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
  }
  
  .intro {
    font-size: 16px;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    font-style: italic;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  
  .description {
    font-size: 15px;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin-bottom: 32px;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  
  .cards-preview {
    display: flex;
    gap: 16px;
    justify-content: center;
    margin: 32px 0;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  
  .preview-card {
    flex: 1;
    min-width: 140px;
    max-width: 180px;
    padding: 20px 12px;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);
    border: 1px dashed rgba(167, 139, 250, 0.3);
    border-radius: 16px;
    opacity: 0.6;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }
  
  .preview-card-emoji {
    font-size: 36px;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  
  .preview-card-label {
    font-family: 'Montserrat', sans-serif;
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  
  .preview-card-meta {
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    margin-top: 4px;
    font-style: italic;
  }
  
  .or-divider {
    font-family: 'Montserrat', sans-serif;
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    align-self: center;
    padding: 0 8px;
  }
  
  .pedagogy-note {
    background: rgba(167, 139, 250, 0.08);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--purple);
    padding: 16px 20px;
    margin: 32px 0;
    text-align: left;
    border-radius: 0 12px 12px 0;
  }
  
  .pedagogy-note-label {
    font-family: 'Montserrat', sans-serif;
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 1.5px;
    color: var(--purple);
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
  
  .pedagogy-note-text {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--ink);
    line-height: 1.65;
  }
  
  .actions {
    margin-top: 36px;
    display: flex;
    gap: 12px;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  
  .btn {
    padding: 12px 24px;
    border-radius: 999px;
    font-family: 'Montserrat', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 13px;
    letter-spacing: 0.5px;
    cursor: pointer;
    border: none;
    text-decoration: none;
    display: inline-block;
    transition: all 0.2s ease;
  }
  
  .btn-primary {
    background: var(--ink);
    color: white;
  }
  
  .btn-primary:hover {
    transform: translateY(-1px);
    box-shadow: 0 4px 12px rgba(26, 29, 43, 0.2);
  }
  
  .btn-secondary {
    background: transparent;
    color: var(--ink);
    border: 1px solid var(--ink-soft);
  }
  
  .btn-secondary:hover {
    background: rgba(26, 29, 43, 0.05);
  }
  
  .progress {
    margin-top: 32px;
    padding-top: 24px;
    border-top: 1px dashed rgba(26, 29, 43, 0.1);
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
  }
  
  .progress-bar {
    background: rgba(26, 29, 43, 0.1);
    height: 6px;
    border-radius: 999px;
    overflow: hidden;
    margin: 8px auto;
    max-width: 200px;
  }
  
  .progress-fill {
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--purple), var(--green));
    height: 100%;
    width: 10%; /* 1 of 10 lessons complete */
    transition: width 0.6s ease;
  }
  
  @media (max-width: 520px) {
    .container { padding: 32px 24px; }
    h1 { font-size: 28px; }
    .cards-preview { flex-direction: column; align-items: center; }
    .preview-card { max-width: 100%; }
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    
    <div class="kicker">🌱 COMING SOON</div>
    
    <div class="lesson-number">FOUNDATION A · LESSON 2</div>
    <h1>Sphere in the Real World</h1>
    
    <!-- Visual: stylized sphere becoming real-world objects -->
    <div class="visual">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 200 100" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
        <defs>
          <radialGradient id="abstract-sphere" cx="35%" cy="30%" r="65%">
            <stop offset="0%" stop-color="#ffffff"/>
            <stop offset="20%" stop-color="#f1f5f9"/>
            <stop offset="60%" stop-color="#94a3b8"/>
            <stop offset="100%" stop-color="#475569"/>
          </radialGradient>
          <radialGradient id="real-apple" cx="35%" cy="30%" r="65%">
            <stop offset="0%" stop-color="#fef3c7"/>
            <stop offset="40%" stop-color="#fbbf24"/>
            <stop offset="100%" stop-color="#92400e"/>
          </radialGradient>
          <radialGradient id="real-orange" cx="35%" cy="30%" r="65%">
            <stop offset="0%" stop-color="#fed7aa"/>
            <stop offset="40%" stop-color="#fb923c"/>
            <stop offset="100%" stop-color="#7c2d12"/>
          </radialGradient>
        </defs>
        
        <!-- Abstract sphere on left -->
        <circle cx="40" cy="50" r="32" fill="url(#abstract-sphere)"/>
        <text x="40" y="92" text-anchor="middle" font-family="Montserrat" font-size="8" font-weight="700" letter-spacing="1" fill="#1a1d2b">ABSTRACT</text>
        
        <!-- Arrow -->
        <line x1="78" y1="50" x2="118" y2="50" stroke="#a78bfa" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-dasharray="3,2"/>
        <polygon points="116,46 124,50 116,54" fill="#a78bfa"/>
        
        <!-- Real-world objects on right (subtle, hinting at choice) -->
        <circle cx="148" cy="38" r="18" fill="url(#real-apple)" opacity="0.7"/>
        <path d="M 148 22 Q 144 18 142 20" stroke="#1d9e75" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>
        
        <circle cx="170" cy="62" r="16" fill="url(#real-orange)" opacity="0.7"/>
        
        <text x="159" y="92" text-anchor="middle" font-family="Montserrat" font-size="8" font-weight="700" letter-spacing="1" fill="#1a1d2b">REAL WORLD</text>
      </svg>
    </div>
    
    <p class="intro">
      You drew an abstract sphere. Now: pick a real spherical object and apply what you've learned.
    </p>
    
    <p class="description">
      In Lesson 2, you'll choose between two real-world objects — like an apple or an orange — and translate the sphere's form principles to something you can hold in your hand.
    </p>
    
    <!-- Preview of the two-card choice mechanic -->
    <div class="cards-preview">
      <div class="preview-card">
        <div class="preview-card-emoji">🍎</div>
        <div class="preview-card-label">Card A</div>
        <div class="preview-card-meta">(or similar)</div>
      </div>
      <div class="or-divider">OR</div>
      <div class="preview-card">
        <div class="preview-card-emoji">🍊</div>
        <div class="preview-card-label">Card B</div>
        <div class="preview-card-meta">(or similar)</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="pedagogy-note">
      <div class="pedagogy-note-label">WHY THIS LESSON</div>
      <p class="pedagogy-note-text">
        Learning shapes in isolation is useful. Seeing the same shape in everyday objects is transformation. The sphere isn't just on the page — it's on your kitchen counter, in the garden, in the fruit bowl. Once you see it, you can't un-see it.
      </p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="actions">
      <a href="../lesson-1-sphere/" class="btn btn-secondary">← Back to Lesson 1</a>
      <a href="../lesson-3-cube/" class="btn btn-primary">Skip to Lesson 3: Cube →</a>
    </div>
    
    <div class="progress">
      <div>Foundation A · 1 of 10 complete</div>
      <div class="progress-bar">
        <div class="progress-fill"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
  </div>
  
  <script>
    // Light tracking — when this placeholder is viewed, we want to know
    console.log('[Lesson 2 Placeholder] Viewed at', new Date().toISOString());
    
    // Check if user has a profile
    try {
      const profile = JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem('fei_user_profile'));
      if (profile && profile.name) {
        // Personalize: change "Back to Lesson 1" to "Continue learning, [Name]"
        console.log('[Lesson 2 Placeholder] Visitor:', profile.name);
      }
    } catch(e) { /* no profile yet */ }
  </script>
</body>
</html>
